  "prompt": "What should be my individual subject scores in NEET 2017?",
  "response": "For NEET 2017, the overall qualifying percentile for the General category was 50th, while for OBC/SC/ST categories, it was 40th and 45th, respectively. However, **there were no specific minimum marks required for individual subjects** (Physics, Chemistry, and Biology) in NEET 2017. Your total score across all subjects was the determining factor for eligibility.\n\nHere\u2019s a general breakdown of the subject-wise distribution and total marks:\n- **Physics**: 45 questions (180 marks)\n- **Chemistry**: 45 questions (180 marks)\n- **Biology (Botany + Zoology)**: 90 questions (360 marks)\n- **Total**: 720 marks\n\nTo qualify, you needed to secure the **minimum qualifying percentile** based on your category. Here\u2019s an approximate idea of the **minimum total scores** required for each category in NEET 2017:\n- **General**: 697-131 marks\n- **OBC**: 130-107 marks\n- **SC**: 130-107 marks\n- **ST**: 130-107 marks\n- **General-PH**: 118-107 marks\n- **OBC/SC/ST-PH**: 118-107 marks\n\nFocus on scoring **at least 50% in Biology** and a balanced score in Physics and Chemistry to maximize your total score. If you\u2019re preparing for NEET, aim for **at least 340+ in Biology** and **120+ in both Physics and Chemistry** to ensure a strong total score.",
